            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_gravity="center_horizontal"
                android:text="House Detection"
                android:textStyle="italic"
                android:textColor="#ffffff"
                android:layout_margin="10dp"
                android:textSize="25sp"/>
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_margin="20dp"
                android:padding="10dp"
                android:text="A house on left side of the road can be detected using SONAR. Sonar is a device which uses ultrasonic waves to detect distance between obstacle and itself. HC-SR05 (Popular Sonar module) emits ultrasonic waves at 40 kHz which travels through the air and if there is an object or obstacle on its path It will bounce back to the module. Considering the travel time and the speed of the sound you can calculate the distance. The HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Module has 4 pins, Ground, VCC, Trig and Echo. In order to generate the ultrasound you need to set the Trig on a High State for 10 Âµs. That will send out 8 cycle sonic burst travelling at the speed of sound and automatically turn the Echo pin high. The Echo pin will be low as soon as the sound comes back as echo. So time between the two will give us the distance of the object from sonar."
                android:textColor="#ccffffff"
                android:background="#9004527e"/>

            <TextView
